The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Friday, April 23, 2004 				 Clash arrests
																								Panrui (Birbhum), April 22: Police arrested 40 people in connection with the violence that erupted here yesterday when residents fought police. 																								Nineteen civilians and seven policemen were injured. The police had to fire several rounds in the air after a lathicharge and tear gas failed to disperse the mob. 																								Local traders have called a business bandh to protest against the arrest of three members of their association. The Trinamul Congress is backing the call.																								Chandan Sen murder: The trial in the murder case of Chandan Sen, a surgeon at Ranaghat Subdivisional Hospital, began in the court of the Nadia district judge. Thirteen months ago, Sen was pulled out from a pond dead.
